<doc id="609901" wikidata="Q4204767" url="?curid=609901" title="TOA Corporation">
<text>is a Japanese electronics company, specializing in public address systems, intercom systems, microphones, array speakers and megaphones. The company&#x27;s products are used in a variety of settings, among them Brompton Oratory, a large neo-classical Roman Catholic church in Knightsbridge, London.

==Early history==
The company was founded in 1934 by Tsunetaro Nakatani as the TOA Electric Manufacturing Company.

